  "prompt": "Can educational testing services (ETS) sponsor cap-exempt H-1B visa?",
  "response": "Yes, Educational Testing Services (ETS) can sponsor cap-exempt H-1B visas. As a non-profit organization associated with higher education, ETS qualifies for H-1B visa cap exemption under the following conditions:\n\n1. ETS is a non-profit research organization affiliated with higher education institutions\n\n2. Cap-exempt status allows them to file H-1B petitions outside of the annual numerical quota\n\n3. They can sponsor foreign workers for specialty occupation positions without being subject to the annual H-1B visa cap\n\n4. Eligible positions typically include research, testing development, educational analysis, and other specialized roles related to their organizational mission\n\nHowever, specific details about sponsorship and current policies would need to be confirmed directly with ETS's human resources or immigration legal team.",
